[According to the data on the Worldometer website, the total number of cases of COVID-19 worldwide is now 1 924 663 with 82 249 (4.3%) cases reported by China. There are now a total of 1 842 414 confirmed cases of COVID-19 reported from 214 countries/locations outside mainland China, representing an increase of 71 419 cases when compared with the data on 12 Apr 2020, with the USA accounting for 26 508 (37.1%), the UK 4342 (6.1%), France 4188 (5.9%), Turkey 4093 (5.7%), Spain 3268 (4.6%), Italy 3153 (4.4%), Germany 2218 (3.1%), Russia 2558 (3.6%), Peru 2265 (3.2%), and Iran 1617 (2.3%) of the newly confirmed cases. The total number of confirmed cases reported from outside China now represents 95.7% of the total number of reported cases. The epicenter has shifted outside of China to Western Europe and the USA. The USA now represents 30.5% of the global cases of COVID-19. A global total of 119 654 deaths have been reported, 116 313 (97.2%) outside mainland China.

The USA is now number one outside China for numbers of confirmed cases of COVID-19, Spain is number 2, and Italy is number 3. While the number of daily new cases in Iran has slowed down, Turkey has shown a rapid increase in the number of cases with 4093 cases reported in the last 24 hours. The case numbers in the UK have also been accelerating, reporting 4342 cases in the past 24 hours. - Mod.MPP]

