[The number of countries and territories reporting confirmed cases of COVID-19 outside China now totals 211. This includes 18 countries (including 4 territories) from the Western Pacific region, 60 countries (including 7 territories) from the European region, 10 from the Southeast Asia region, 22 countries (including 1 territory) from the Eastern Mediterranean region, 54 countries (including 19 territories) from the Americas region, and 47 countries (including 2 territories) from the African region.

The Americas region is reporting 36 804 new cases (in the past 24 hours) of which 85.9% were reported by the USA, followed by Canada (3.1%) and Brazil (3.0%). Recognizing the USA data are overshadowing the regional proportions, without including the reported newly confirmed cases from the USA, Canada reported 22.4% of the newly reported cases in the region, followed by Brazil at 21.1%, Peru at 18.4%, Mexico at 7.3%, and the Dominican Republic at 6.7%.

The European region was slower, possibly related to the Easter weekend, having confirmed 33 243 (43.5% of the global newly reported cases) new cases and 3183 (55.8%) deaths in the 24 hours since the last WHO update. The UK reported 15.9% of newly confirmed cases, Turkey 14.4%, Spain 12.5%, Italy 12.3%, Germany 7.6%, and France 4.8%. Russia accounted for 7.7% of the newly confirmed cases, more than France and Germany. Those 6 countries (UK, Spain, Turkey, Italy, Germany, and France, representing 10% of the European countries) account for 67.6% of newly confirmed cases in Europe.

In the Eastern Mediterranean region, Iran reported 1657 new cases representing 44.0%% of the regional newly reported cases. Saudi Arabia, the United Arab Emirates (UAE), Pakistan, and Qatar represent 11.4%, 10.3%, 8.9%, and 6.7% respectively. Removing Iran from the denominator, Saudi Arabia represents 20.3% of newly confirmed cases, followed by the UAE at 20.0%, Pakistan at 18.3%, and Qatar at 11.9%.

In the African region, Ghana reported 29.8% of the newly reported cases in the region in the past 24 hours, followed by South Africa at 27.3%, Algeria at 16.8%, and Niger at 7.2%.

In the Western Pacific region, Japan reported 42.4% of the newly reported cases (outside of China), Singapore 19.5%, the Philippines 18.4%, and Malaysia 12.8%.

In South East Asia, 4 of the 10 countries reported no new cases in the previous 24 hours (including Bangladesh and Indonesia, countries that have been reporting daily increases). Of the remaining countries, India reported 94.5% of newly reported cases.

Figure 2. Epidemic curve of confirmed COVID-19 cases reported outside of China, by date of report and WHO region through [13 Apr 2020], at the source URL above, is an excellent representation of the epidemic starting in the Western Pacific, transitioning to multiregional activity as the virus travelled. One sees the contribution of the ongoing epidemics in Europe and now the increasing cases in the Americas region, fueled by the USA but other countries are following suit. The curve dropped over the weekend, although the America's region did not appear to drop. Consistent with prior weekend reporting drops.

A somewhat repetitive but necessary reminder: it is clear that the number of reported confirmed cases differs from different reporting websites and is somewhat a function of time of day the website is updated. For example, I note the time we've accessed the Worldometer website, but by the time the post is actually finished with the editing process, those numbers have at times significantly changed. Case counting is clearly a moving target, and, depending upon when the website updates, the numbers may be different. I try to start each post with the latest figures for the calendar day (the Worldometer table) and close with the figures from the start of the calendar day (the WHO tables), defining the calendar day as DST (now GMT-4).

For the past 3 weeks, I have had help compiling all of the data presented in the tables and preparing spreadsheets, and want to publicly thank Coleman Schaefer for his amazing assistance -- a formidable task to say the least. - Mod.MPP]
